Tiwa who is about to drop her first official single of 2019 is to perform at the DSTV’s Delicious Festival in Johannesburg, but it now appears that won’t be happening as she has revealed she is pulling out of the show in order to protest the killings of Nigerians and other foreign nationals in South Africa. She wrote; ” I refuse to watch the barbaric butchering of my people in SA. This is SICK. For this reason I will NOT be performing at the upcoming DSTV delicious Festival in Johannesburg on the 21st of September. My prayers are with all the victims and families affected by this.”  Tiwa Savage joins the list of other Nigerian artistes who have decided to “cancel” South Africa until they are able to profer a solution to the issue of Xenophobia which has plagued the countru for a number of years. The post Tiwa Savage Pulls Out Of A Show In South Africa Over Xenophobic Attacks On Nigerians appeared first on tooXclusive. Source: Too Xclusive Tiwa Savage Tiwa Savage has canceled her upcoming show in Johannesburg, South Africa due to the ongoing Xenophobic crisis in the country against Nigerians and other African nations. The ‘One’ singer who is meant to perform in South Africa on the 21st of September made her stance clear earlier today,… September 4, 2019 In "Music/Video" Singer Tiwa Savage is devastated with the killings and looting of Nigerians and other African nationals in South Africa. Tiwa has  cancelled her performance at the upcoming DStv Delicious Festival in Johannesburg on the 21st of September. Sending her prayers to victims on her Twitter handle, she wrote: I refuse… September 4, 2019 In "Entertainment" Nigerian music diva, Tiwa Savage has taken to her Twitter account to announce that she will not be performing in South Africa later this month as earlier scheduled. The 'African Waist' crooner made this known in the wake of the recent xenophobic attacks on Nigerians by South Africans that has… September 4, 2019 In "News"